<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Given that the characteristics of the type specimen of 
<taxonomicName authority="A.Berlese, 1904" authorityName="A.Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Ameroseiidae" genus="Ameroseius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ameroseius longitarsis" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longitarsis">Ameroseius longitarsis</taxonomicName>
are within the range of variability found in 
<taxonomicName authority="A.Berlese, 1904" authorityName="A.Berlese" authorityYear="1904" class="Arachnida" family="Ameroseiidae" genus="Ameroseius" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Ameroseius benoiti" order="Mesostigmata" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="benoiti">Ameroseius benoiti</taxonomicName>
Elsen, 1973, I suspect 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. longitarsis" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="longitarsis">A. longitarsis</taxonomicName>
to be a synonym of 
<taxonomicName genus="A." lsidName="A. benoiti" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="benoiti">A. benoiti</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
